on}}\n| {{NYCS Lexington local night|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Sixth night|time=show}} ([[IND Sixth Avenue Line]] at [[Broadway\u2013Lafayette Street (IND Sixth Avenue Line)|Broadway\u2013Lafayette Street]])\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=center |\u2191\n|align=center |\u2193\n| [[Spring Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Spring Street]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Lexington local night|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=center |\u2191\n|align=center |\u2193\n| [[Canal Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Canal Street]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Lexington local night|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Broadway night|time=show}} ([[BMT Broadway Line]])<br />{{NYCS Nassau north night|time=show}} ([[BMT Nassau Street Line]])\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Brooklyn Bridge\u2013City Hall (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Brooklyn Bridge\u2013City Hall]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Lexington|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Nassau north|time=show}} ([[BMT Nassau Street Line]] at [[Chambers Street (BMT Nassau Street Line)|Chambers Street]])\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Fulton Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Fulton Street]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Lexington south|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Broadway-Seventh Brooklyn|time=show}} ([[IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line]])<br />{{NYCS Cranberry|time=show}} ([[IND Eighth Avenue Line]])<br />{{NYCS Nassau south|time=show}} ([[BMT Nassau Street Line]])\n| Connection to {{NYCS Broadway south|time=show}} ([[BMT Broadway Line]]) at [[Cortlandt Street (BMT Broadway Line)|Cortlandt Street]] via [[Dey Street Passageway]]\n[[Port Authority Trans-Hudson|PATH]] at [[World Trade Center (PATH station)|World Trade Center]]\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Wall Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Wall Street]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Lexington south|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Bowling Green (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Bowling Green]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Lexington south|time=show|exclude=4}}\n| [[Select Bus Service#M15 |M15 Select Bus Service]]\n[[Staten Island Ferry]] at [[Staten Island Ferry Whitehall Terminal|Whitehall Terminal]] <br> Southern terminus of two a.m. rush hour trips and special event express service\n|-\n| style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" | [[Brooklyn]]\n|-\n| style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" | [[IRT Eastern Parkway Line|Eastern Parkway Line]]\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n|align=center rowspan=\"10\" {{n/a}}\n| [[Borough Hall (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Borough Hall]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}&nbsp;\u2191\n| {{NYCS Lexington Brooklyn|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Broadway-Seventh Brooklyn|time=show}} ([[IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line]])<br />{{NYCS Fourth north|time=show}} ([[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]])\n| Station is [[Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990|ADA-accessible]] in the northbound direction only.\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[Nevins Street (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Nevins Street]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Eastern west|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Eastern west|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Brighton north|time=show}} ([[BMT Brighton Line]])<br />{{NYCS Fourth center|time=show}} ([[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]])\n| [[Long Island Rail Road|LIRR]] [[Atlantic Branch]] at [[Atlantic Terminal (LIRR station)|Atlantic Terminal]]\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=\"center\"|\u2191\n| [[Bergen Street (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Bergen Street]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Eastern west local night|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=\"center\"|\u2191\n| [[Grand Army Plaza (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Grand Army Plaza]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Eastern west local night|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=\"center\"|\u2191\n| [[Eastern Parkway\u2013Brooklyn Museum (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Eastern Parkway\u2013Brooklyn Museum]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Eastern west local night|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[Franklin Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Franklin Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS Eastern west|time=show|exclude=4}}<br />{{NYCS Franklin|time=show}} ([[BMT Franklin Avenue Line]])\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=\"center\"|\u2191\n| [[Nostrand Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Nostrand Avenue]]\n|\n|\n| [[B44 SBS (New York City bus)|B44 Select Bus Service]]\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n|align=\"center\"|\u2191\n| [[Kingston Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Kingston Avenue]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Eastern center|time=show|exclude=4}}\n| [[B46 SBS (New York City bus)|B46 Select Bus Service]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" bgcolor=\"#808080\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" | '''[[IRT New Lots Line|New Lots Line]]''' (late nights and select rush hour trips)\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| align=center rowspan=7 colspan=\"2\" {{N/A}}\n| [[Sutter Avenue\u2013Rutland Road (IRT New Lots Line)|Sutter Avenue\u2013Rutland Road]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n| [[B15 (New York City bus)|B15]] bus to [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|JFK Int'l Airport]]<br />\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Saratoga Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|Saratoga Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Rockaway Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|Rockaway Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Junius Street (IRT New Lots Line)|Junius Street]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}<br>Out-of-system transfer with [[MetroCard]] during nights and weekends: {{NYCS Canarsie|time=show}} ([[BMT Canarsie Line]] at [[Livonia Avenue (BMT Canarsie Line)|Livonia Avenue]])\n| \n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Pennsylvania Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|Pennsylvania Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[Van Siclen Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|Van Siclen Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n|\n|-\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrushpeak}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[New Lots Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]]\n|\n| {{NYCS New Lots|time=show|exclude=4}}\n| [[B15 (New York City bus)|B15]] bus to [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|JFK Int'l Airport]]\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|4 (New York City Subway service)}}\n* [http://web.mta.info/nyct/service/fourline.htm MTA NYC Transit \u2013 4 Lexington Avenue Express]\n* {{NYCS const|traintime|4}}\n* {{NYCS const|timetable|4}}\n\n{{NYCS navbox}}\n\n[[Category:Interborough Rapid Transit Company|#]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway services]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the former Brooklyn\u2013Manhattan Transit Corporation 4 service|N (New York City Subway service)}}\n{{Infobox NYCS service\n| service    = 4\n| name       = Lexington Avenue Express\n| image1     = 4 train leaving Harlem on August night.jpg\n| size1 = 250px\n| caption1 = Bronx-bound '''4''' train of [[R142A (New York City Subway car)|R142As]] leaving [[125th Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|125th Street]].\n| north term = [[Woodlawn (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Woodlawn]]\n| south term = [[Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue]] (daytime) <br />[[New Lots Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]] (late nights & limited rush hour service)\n| stations   = 28<br />54 (late night service)\n| note       = dashed line shows late night and limited weekday rush hour service to/from [[New Lots Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]]\n| depot      = [[Jerome Yard|Jerome Avenue Yard]]\n| started    = {{start date and age|1917|06|02}}\n| map        = {{4 (New York City Subway service)}}\n| map_state  = collapsed\n}}\nThe '''4 Lexington Avenue Express'''<ref name=\"timetable\">{{NYCS const|timetable|4}}</ref> is a [[rapid transit]] service in the [[A Division (New York City Subway)|A Division]] of the [[New York City Subway]]. Its route emblem, or \"bullet\", is colored {{NYCS const|color|green}} since it uses the [[IRT Lexington Avenue Line]] in [[Manhattan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/developers/resources/line_colors.htm|title=mta.info &#124; Line Colors|website=web.mta.info}}</ref>\n\nThe '''4''' operates at all times. Daytime service operates between [[Woodlawn (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Woodlawn]] in [[the Bronx]] and [[Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Utica Avenue]] in [[Crown Heights, Brooklyn]], via [[IRT Jerome Avenue Line|Jerome Avenue Local]] in the Bronx, Lexington Avenue Express in Manhattan, and [[IRT Eastern Parkway Line|Eastern Parkway Express]] in Brooklyn; limited rush hour service, as well as late night service, is extended beyond Utica Avenue to/from [[New Lots Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]] in [[East New York, Brooklyn]] via [[IRT New Lots Line|Livonia Avenue]]. During rush hours in the peak direction, '''4''' trains skip [[138th Street\u2013Grand Concourse (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|138th Street\u2013Grand Concourse]].{{efn|Trains skip 138th Street southbound between 6:52 and 9 a.m. and skip it northbound between 4:50 and 6:25 p.m.|name=138th Street}} Late night service makes all stops except for [[Hoyt Street (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Hoyt Street]]. For up to an hour after evening events that are held at [[Yankee Stadium]], a special downtown-only express service runs between {{Station|161st Street\u2013Yankee Stadium}} and {{Station|Bowling Green}}.\n\nUntil 1983, rush hour '''4''' trains originated and terminated at [[Flatbush Avenue\u2013Brooklyn College (IRT Nostrand Avenue Line)|Flatbush Avenue\u2013Brooklyn College]] in [[Brooklyn]].\n\n== Service history ==\n\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\">\n{| width=\"80\"\n[[File:R12 IRT 4.gif|64px]]\n|-\n|<div class=\"thumbcaption\"> Original [[R12 (New York City Subway car)|R12]] to [[R36 (New York City Subway car)|R36]] end rollsign</div>\n|}\n</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\">\n{| width=\"80\"\n[[File:4 (1967-1979 New York City Subway bullet).svg]]\n|-\n|<div class=\"thumbcaption\">November 26, 1967-June 1979 bullet</div>\n|}\n</div>\n\n===Under the Interborough Rapid Transit===\nService on what was later known as the '''4''' began on June 2, 1917, as the first portion of the [[IRT Jerome Avenue Line]] opened between 149th Street\u2014Grand Concourse and Kingsbridge Road. Since the extension of the [[IRT Lexington Avenue Line]] between 149th Street and Grand Central was not yet open, this section was served by shuttle trains using elevated train cars.<ref name=\"erictb.info\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.erictb.info/linehistory.html|title=NYCT Line by Line History|website=erictb.info|access-date=September 23, 2016}}</ref> On April 15, 1918, with the extension of the Jerome Avenue Line to Woodlawn, shuttle service was also extended. On July 17, 1918, the Lexington Avenue Line local tracks were opened, allowing another shuttle service to run between 149th Street\u2013Grand Concourse and Grand Central. On August 1, 1918, the entire Jerome and Lexington Avenue Lines were completed and the connection to the [[IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line]] at 42nd Street was removed. Trains began running between 167th Street and Bowling Green, with shuttles to Woodlawn.<ref name=\"erictb.info\" />\n\nOn December 11, 1921, Lexington Avenue\u2013Jerome Avenue subway trains began running north of [[167th Street station (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|167th Street]] at all times, replacing elevated trains, which ran to Woodlawn during rush hours, but from then on terminated at 167th Street during non-rush hours.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pudl.princeton.edu/sheetreader.php?obj=e75de858-4334-4238-bc92-399e37286bbb|title=An Improvement in Service for Passengers on the Jerome Avenue Line North of 167th Street|last=|first=|date=December 11, 1921|website=pudl.princeton.edu|publisher=Interborough Rapid Transit Company|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=September 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt a hearing of the New York State Transit Commission on October 15, 1924 about where it planned to allocate the second hundred of 350 new steel cars, it was announced that service on the IRT Eastern Parkway Line from Atlantic Avenue to Livonia Avenue was almost certainly going to be increased by 25 to 50% in the coming six to eight weeks. Two options were discussed at the hearing. The commission, in response to intense requests from riders on the line, called for the introduction of express service between Atlantic Avenue and Utica Avenue on tracks which had been unused since the line's opening in 1920. It proposed extending half of '''4''' trains from Atlantic Avenue to New Lots Avenue, running express to Utica Avenue. The introduction of express service would have made it possible to run 30 more trains per hour east of Atlantic Avenue (27 trains per hour had been operating), decreasing overcrowding from 325% to 185%. The plan preferred by the IRT was to place 70 cars on the West Side Line for service to Flatbush Avenue, and Pennsylvania Avenue and New Lots Avenue, and 40 additional cars for service along Eastern Parkway.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35414638/times-union/|title=I.R.T. Will Get Increased Service To Livonia Avenue: Practically Certain That 100 New Cars Will Be Put on Eastern Parkway Line.|date=October 16, 1924|work=Brooklyn Times Union|access-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nOn November 17, 1924, the Transit Commission ordered the IRT to use 100 new subway cars to increase service by no later than December 1. Among the changes in service ordered was the operation of through service on the '''4''' between Kingsbridge Road and Woodlawn, eliminating shuttle service.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35414795/times-union/|title=Transit Board Orders I.R.T. To Increase Service: Demands More Trains in Rush Hour by Use of New Cars.|date=November 17, 1924|work=Brooklyn Times Union|access-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> This change was made possible by 20 of the new cars.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35414748/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=100 I.R.T. Cars To Be Used On Borough Lines|date=November 17, 1924|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The Transit Commission headed the IRT's recommendation not to have half of '''4''' trains run express due to the dangerous operating condition it would have created. The IRT stated that two minutes would not be enough time to turn around trains terminating at Atlantic Avenue while maintaining the headway between trains and that this service pattern would risk train collisions. Operating this service pattern would have required 2 minutes and 45 seconds to turn around trains, which would reduce capacity by 25%. While operating all '''4''' trains to Utica Avenue would have obviated the problem, the IRT did not have enough cars to run such a service. Instead, the Transit Commission accepted the IRT's plan to allocate 70 new cars to West Side express service to Brooklyn.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35414788/the-standard-union/|title=Orders I.R.T. to Improve Service|date=November 17, 1924|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Express service along Eastern Parkway would start at the earliest in February 1925 when additional new cars arrived.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35414740/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=Hundred I.R.T. Cars To Bring Big Relief In Eastern Parkway: New Equipment, Recently Delivered, Will Increase Service 30 Per Cent. On Important Borough Lines, Commissioner McAneny Announces. Opening of Express Service Between Utica and Atlantic Aves. Off 3 Months.|date=November 17, 1924|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBeginning on November 4, 1925, '''4''' trains were extended from Atlantic Avenue to [[Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue]] during rush hours, from 6:30 to 9:30 a.m. and 5 and 7 p.m., allowing for the introduction of express service along this section of the [[IRT Eastern Parkway Line]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pudl.princeton.edu/sheetreader.php?obj=f5217622-5c01-49b6-b3d1-bef13f813a0a|title=Increased I.R.T. Subway Service in Brooklyn|last=|first=|date=November 1925|website=pudl.princeton.edu|publisher=Interborough Rapid Transit Company|access-date=2016-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/46595852/the-standard-union/|title=At Least I.R.T. Expresses Will Run Under Parkway: Two Tracks Will End Their Long Career of Idleness a Week from Wednesday.|date=October 25, 1925|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> This extension was made possible by the delivery of the last of 350 new steel cars.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/35415064/the-standard-union/|title=More I.R.T. Trains For Rush Hours To Operate Tomorrow: Brooklyn Gets Improved Service at cost of $3,000,000\u2014President Hedley Makes Inspection Trip.|date=November 3, 1925|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The increased service required 80 cars, or eight trains of ten cars each.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/46596083/times-union/|title=I.R.T. Will Start Express Service In Boro Nov. 4: Ninety New Cars Added on Flatbush Ave. and Eastern Parkway Lines. Rush Hour Aid First. Three Million Dollar Outlay Will Mean 20 to 100 P.C. Better Handling of Crowds.|date=October 25, 1925|work=Brooklyn Times Union|access-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nOn November 23, 1927, evening '''4''' service was extended from Atlantic Avenue to Utica Avenue between 7:14 and 8 p.m.. After the Transit Commission determined that this was not a sufficient increase in service, it announced on November 26 that evening '''4''' service to Utica Avenue would continue until 1 a.m.. This change took place on December 5, and increased service between Atlantic Avenue and Utica Avenue by 100%.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/46594743/times-union/|title=100 P.C. Increase In I.R.T. Service: More Trains on Schedule Between Atlantic and Utica Avenues at Night.|date=November 27, 1927|work=Brooklyn Times Union|access-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following year, midday '''4''' service also went to Utica Avenue.<ref name=\"erictb.info\" />\n\nAs of 1934, '''4''' trains ran from Woodlawn to Utica Avenue weekday rush and Saturday morning peak and afternoon, to Atlantic Avenue weekday midday, Saturday morning after the peak, and late nights, and to South Ferry evenings and Sundays. Trains ran express in Manhattan except during late nights, and in Brooklyn. This was the first time the '''6''' became the Pelham Shuttle between Pelham Bay Park and 125th Street\u2013Lexington Avenue.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nOn August 20, 1938, Saturday morning after the peak service was extended to Utica Avenue.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\n===Under the New York City Board of Transportation===\n\nBeginning on May 10, 1946, all '''4''' trains were made express during late nights running on 12 minute headways as the '''6''' went back to Brooklyn Bridge during that time. Previously '''4''' trains ran local from 12:30 to 5:30am. At this time '''4''' trains terminated at Atlantic Avenue.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1946/05/09/100997388.pdf|title = 24-Hour Express Service on IRT To Become Effective at Midnight|last = |first = |date = May 9, 1946|work = |access-date = February 21, 2016|via = |newspaper = New York Times}}</ref><ref name=\"BOT-1949\">{{Cite book|title=Report for the three and one-half years ending June 30, 1949.|date=1949|publisher=New York City Board of Transportation|hdl = 2027/mdp.39015023094926}}</ref>\n\nBeginning on December 16, 1946, trains were extended from Atlantic Avenue to New Lots Avenue during late nights, running express between Atlantic and Franklin Avenues.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1946/12/12/305817632.pdf|title = City to Increase Subway Service On the IRT and BMT Lines Today|last = |first = |date = December 12, 1946|work = |access-date = February 21, 2016|via = |newspaper = New York Times}}</ref>\n\nThe [[New York City Board of Transportation]], a predecessor to the [[New York City Transit Authority]], began to introduce replacements to older subway cars beginning with the [[R12 (New York City Subway car)|R12]] cars in 1948. With these cars, numbers were publicly designated to the former IRT lines. Lexington\u2013Jerome trains were assigned the number '''4'''. By 1964, all cars had the route numbers on them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thejoekorner.com/lines/suball-frame.htm|title=Line Names|website=thejoekorner.com|access-date=September 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\nDuring 1950, Saturday morning service was cut back to South Ferry.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nStarting on December 15, 1950, four '''4''' trains began operating during rush hours to [[Flatbush Avenue\u2013Brooklyn College (IRT Nostrand Avenue Line)|Flatbush Avenue]] on the [[IRT Nostrand Avenue Line|Nostrand Avenue Line]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1950/12/15/313761962.pdf|title=Brooklyn I.R.T. Change; 4 Lexington Avenue Expresses to Serve Flatbush Station|date=December 15, 1950|work=The New York Times|newspaper=|access-date=February 22, 2016|url-status=live|via=}}</ref> Also on that day, weekday midday service was cut back from Atlantic Avenue to South Ferry. Additionally, on January 18, 1952, '''4''' service to Atlantic Avenue during weekday middays was restored.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1952/01/10/93341886.pdf|title = Changes on I.R.T. Set: Additional Express Service on Brooklyn, Flushing Lines Day|last = |first = |date = January 10, 1952|work = |access-date = January 25, 2016|via = |newspaper = New York Times}}</ref>\n\n===Under the New York City Transit Authority===\n\nOn March 19, 1954, late-night service in Brooklyn became local, but resumed operating express between Atlantic and Franklin Avenues on June 29, 1956.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nOn May 3, 1957, the weekday rush trains to Flatbush Avenue were discontinued, while at the same time evening, Saturday and Sunday afternoon trains were extended to Utica Avenue, while Sunday morning trains were extended to Atlantic Avenue.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nStarting on March 1, 1960, late-night '''4''' trains resumed making all stops in Manhattan; this was the first time the '''4''' and '''6''' ran local in Manhattan together late nights. This arrangement ended on October 17, 1965, when the '''4''' went back express in Manhattan late nights.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nBeginning on April 8, 1960, nearly all AM rush hour '''4''' trains ran to Flatbush Avenue, and PM rush hour '''4''' trains alternated between Flatbush and Utica Avenues. During weekday evenings and late nights '''4''' trains also went to Flatbush Avenue, making all stops in Brooklyn.<ref name=\"erictb.info\" />\n\nAs a result of the opening of the main portion of the [[Chrystie Street Connection]] along the [[Manhattan Bridge]] on November 26, 1967, the '''4''' train was color-coded magenta under the first color scheme. The color coding of lines was introduced as a matter of having a universal system of signage and nomenclature.\n\nBy 1972, the '''4''' began to skip 138th Street weekdays during rush hours in the peak direction which it continues to do (AM to Manhattan and PM from there). At that time, the '''4''' went to Atlantic Avenue at all times, but was extended to Utica Avenue rush hours running express in Brooklyn along Eastern Parkway. Select '''4''' trains also ran to Flatbush Avenue rush hours as well running express between Atlantic and Franklin Avenues, and late-night service made all stops in Brooklyn to Flatbush Avenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/caption.pl?/img/maps/system_1972.jpg|title=1972 New York City Subway Map|last=|first=|date=1972|website=nycsubway.org|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn May 23, 1976, Sunday morning trains were extended to Utica Avenue, running express in Brooklyn.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nEffective June 1979, the '''4''' train assumed its current line color of forest green as a result of a nomenclature update to assign colors to a trunk line, plus line colors not serving Manhattan.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nBeginning on January 13, 1980, all '''4''' trains resumed operating local in Manhattan during late night hours to replace the '''{{NYCS|6}}''', which again became the Pelham Shuttle between [[125th Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|125th Street]] and [[Pelham Bay Park (IRT Pelham Line)|Pelham Bay Park]].<ref name=\"erictb.info\" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=December 1979|title=January 1980 IRT Service Changes|url=|journal=New York Division Bulletin|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> This service cut affected 15,000 riders, and was criticized by Manhattan Borough President [[Andrew Stein]] as no public hearing was held.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/433946217/?terms=%22subway%22%2B%22service%2Bcut%22|title=Suit seeks to bar cutbacks on Lexington Ave. subways|last=|first=|date=January 11, 1980|work=New York Daily News|access-date=August 14, 2018|page=}}</ref>\n\nOn July 10, 1983, rush hour '''4''' trains were rerouted from Flatbush Avenue to Utica Avenue, and late evening and late night and Sunday morning service was rerouted from Flatbush Avenue to New Lots Avenue, making all local stops.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=July 1983|title=New IRT Schedules - Increased Service to Flatbush Avenue|url=|journal=New York Division Bulletin|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://fultonhistory.com/highlighter/highlight-for-xml?altUrl=https%3A%2F%2Ffultonhistory.com%2FNewspaper%252024%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%25201983%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%25201983%252000253_1.pdf%23xml%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ffultonhistory.com%2FdtSearch%2Fdtisapi6.dll%3Fcmd%3Dgetpdfhits%26u%3Dffffffffa28002b6%26DocId%3D6932839%26Index%3DZ%253a%255cDISK%2520X%26HitCount%3D11%26hits%3D5fa%2B5fb%2B5fc%2B5fd%2B5fe%2B5ff%2B600%2B601%2B602%2B603%2B604%2B%26SearchForm%3D%252fFulton%255fform%252ehtml%26.pdf&uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffultonhistory.com%2FNewspaper%252024%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%25201983%2FNew%2520York%2520NY%2520Amsterdam%2520News%25201983%252000253_1.pdf&xml=https%3A%2F%2Ffultonhistory.com%2FdtSearch%2Fdtisapi6.dll%3Fcmd%3Dgetpdfhits%26u%3Dffffffffa28002b6%26DocId%3D6932839%26Index%3DZ%253a%255cDISK%2520X%26HitCount%3D11%26hits%3D5fa%2B5fb%2B5fc%2B5fd%2B5fe%2B5ff%2B600%2B601%2B602%2B603%2B604%2B%26SearchForm%3D%252fFulton%255fform%252ehtml%26.pdf&openFirstHlPage=false|title=Notice of Public Hearing|last=|first=|date=February 26, 1983|work=New York Amsterdam News|access-date=January 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn August 29, 1988, weekday midday '''4''' trains were extended from Atlantic Avenue to Utica Avenue, made possible by the termination of '''5''' service at Bowling Green.<ref name=\"1989Changes\" /><ref name=\"erictb.info\" /> In addition, service was increased 50% during evenings between 8 p.m. and midnight, on Saturday afternoon and on Sunday between 10 a.m. and 7 p.m. In January 1989, during middays, southbound service resumed operating express between Franklin Avenue and Utica Avenue following the elimination of '''5''' train layups.<ref name=\"1989Changes\" />\n\nLate night express service was reinstated from January 21, 1990 to October 5 of that year, as a result of the '''6''' being extended back to Brooklyn Bridge during that time.<ref name=\"1989Changes\">*{{Cite book|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/46694885825/in/album-72157706539432321/|title=Annual Report on 1989 Rapid Routes Schedules and Service Planning|last=|first=|date=June 1, 1990|publisher=New York City Transit Authority, Operations Planning Department|year=|isbn=|location=|page=26}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/46694885115/in/album-72157706539432321/|title=Annual Report on 1989 Rapid Routes Schedules and Service Planning|last=|first=|date=June 1, 1990|publisher=New York City Transit Authority, Operations Planning Department|year=|isbn=|location=|page=27}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/40644004553/in/album-72157706539432321/|title=Annual Report on 1989 Rapid Routes Schedules and Service Planning|last=|first=|date=June 1, 1990|publisher=New York City Transit Authority, Operations Planning Department|year=|isbn=|location=|page=28}}\n</ref> While late night '''6''' service to Brooklyn Bridge was permanently restored on October 3, 1999, the '''4''' continued to run local at those times, providing Lexington Avenue local stations service every ten minutes.<ref name=\"1999Change\">\n* {{cite book|title=May 1999 NYC Transit Committee Agenda|date=May 13, 1999|website=Flickr|accessdate=March 13, 2020|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/48536123271/in/photostream/|page=144}}\n* {{cite book|title=May 1999 NYC Transit Committee Agenda|date=May 13, 1999|website=Flickr|accessdate=March 13, 2020|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/48536270792/in/photostream/|page=145-146}}\n* {{cite book|title=May 1999 NYC Transit Committee Agenda|date=May 13, 1999|website=Flickr|accessdate=March 13, 2020|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/48536269727/in/photostream/|page=147}}\n* {{cite book|title=May 1999 NYC Transit Committee Agenda|date=May 13, 1999|website=Flickr|accessdate=March 13, 2020|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/48536268767/in/photostream/|page=148}}\n* {{cite book|title=May 1999 NYC Transit Committee Agenda|date=May 13, 1999|website=Flickr|accessdate=March 13, 2020|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/127872292@N06/48536267922/in/photostream/|page=149}}</ref>\n\n=== Recent changes ===\n[[File: Manhattan bound R142 4 train enters Yankee Stadium.jpg|thumb|Manhattan-bound '''4''' train of [[R142 (New York City Subway car)|R142s]] entering [[161st Street\u2013Yankee Stadium (New York City Subway)|161st Street\u2013Yankee Stadium]]]]\n\nFrom April 2000 to August 2001, midday '''4''' service was temporarily cut back from Utica Avenue to Atlantic Avenue to accommodate the rebuilding of the [[IRT New Lots Line]].<ref>{{Citation|url=|title=Timetable for subway service on the 4 Train Effective Spring 2000|last=|first=|date=April 2000|website=|publisher=New York City Transit|access-date=}}</ref> '''3''' train service was split into two sections to allow for the line to be rebuilt, with transfers available at Utica Avenue. Work took place on weekday middays between 10 a.m. and 3 p.m., and New Lots service operated in one of three ways: shuttle buses replaced trains, all trains operated in both directions on a single track, or shuttle trains ran. '''4''' trains terminated at Atlantic Avenue when shuttle or single-track trains were in operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us/nyct/service/subsrvno.htm#FourLine|title=Weekly Subway Service Advisories Updated Nov 9, 2000|last=|first=|date=2000-11-09|website=mta.nyc.ny.us|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20001109144600/http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us/nyct/service/subsrvno.htm#FourLine|archive-date=November 9, 2000|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nFrom June 8, 2009, to June 26, 2009, New York City Transit conducted a pilot program for express Jerome Avenue Line service. During a one hour period, four morning weekday rush hour trains from Woodlawn only stopped at Mosholu Parkway, Burnside Avenue and 149th Street\u2013Grand Concourse before resuming regular service in Manhattan and Brooklyn. The express was expected to save riders 3.5 minutes. The pilot was made possible due to signaling upgrades to the line's center track made as part of the 2005\u20142009 Metropolitan Transportation Authority Capital Program.<ref name=\"MTA-June2009Pilot\">{{cite press release|title=MTA New York City Transit Pilots Bronx Express Service Along the Jerome Ave. Line|url=http://www.mta.info/press-release/nyc-transit/mta-new-york-city-transit-pilots-bronx-express-service-along-jerome-ave|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|date=June 4, 2009|accessdate=June 8, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/events/BronxExpressPilot.htm|title=Bronx Express Pilot Program June 8 to 26, Monday to Friday, 7 AM to 8 AM|last=|first=|date=June 10, 2009|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090610212200/http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/events/BronxExpressPilot.htm|archivedate=June 10, 2009|access-date=September 23, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n\nOn July 6, 2009, select Bronx bound '''4''' trains began running express from 167th Street to Burnside Avenue to terminate at the latter station before running out of service to the Jerome Yard.\n\nOn October 26, 2009, another '''4''' express pilot program was implemented based on the success of the first and ran until December 11, 2009. This program was the same as the one in June except that express trains stopped at [[Bedford Park Boulevard\u2013Lehman College (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Bedford Park Boulevard\u2013Lehman College]]. This express service was expected to cut runtime by four minutes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/events/BronxExpressPilot.htm|title=Bronx Express Phase II October 26 to December 11, Monday to Friday, 7 AM to 8:20 AM|last=|first=|date=November 22, 2009|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091122100652/http://www.mta.info/nyct/service/events/BronxExpressPilot.htm|archivedate=November 22, 2009|access-date=September 23, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n\nAs a result of planned repairs to [[Hurricane Sandy]]-related damage in the Clark Street Tube, which carries the [[IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line]], on weekends from June 17, 2017 to June 24, 2018, the '''4''' was extended to New Lots Avenue on weekends, making local stops in Brooklyn south of [[Nevins Street (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Nevins Street]] in place of the {{NYCS|3}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/161212_1000_Transit.pdf|title=Transit & Bus Committee Meeting December 2016|last=|first=|date=December 12, 2016|website=mta.info|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|pages=PDF\u2013169 to PDF\u2013175|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161210041234/http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/161212_1000_Transit.pdf|archivedate=December 10, 2016|accessdate=December 9, 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/sandy/sandy_recovery_work.htm|title=Clark St Tunnel Reconstruction Weekend Service Changes|last=|first=|date=June 8, 2017|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170608184832/http://web.mta.info/sandy/sandy_recovery_work.htm|archive-date=June 8, 2017|access-date=May 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn November 17, 2019, New York City Transit cut weekday evening '''3''', '''4''' and '''5''' service in order to accommodate planned subway work. This change, which was approved by the MTA Board on June 27, 2019, started late night '''4''' service to New Lots Avenue, an hour earlier, at 10:30 p.m. instead of 11:30 p.m., replacing '''3''' service, which was cut back to [[Times Square\u201342nd Street/Port Authority Bus Terminal station|Times Square\u201342nd Street]]. These changes in service were expected to save the agency $0.9 million annually.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/190624_1030_Transit.pdf|title=Transit and Bus Committee Meeting June 2019|last=|first=|date=June 24, 2019|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|page=94-97|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://new.mta.info/document/9446|title=5 Subway Timetable Effective November 17, 2019|last=|first=|date=November 17, 2019|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Route ==\n\n=== Service pattern ===\nThe following table shows the lines used by the '''4''', with shaded boxes indicating the route at the specified times:<ref>{{NYCS const|serviceguide}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n! rowspan=2 | Line\n! rowspan=2 | From\n! rowspan=2 | To\n! rowspan=2 | Tracks\n! colspan=3 | Times\n|-\n! width=40 | all {{abbr|ex.|except}} nights\n! width=40 | late nights\n! width=40 | rush peak\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[IRT Jerome Avenue Line]] (full line)\n| [[Woodlawn (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Woodlawn]]\n|[[183rd Street station (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|183rd Street]]\n| rowspan=2 | local\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ddffdd;\" | Most trains\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Burnside Avenue station|Burnside Avenue]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[170th Street station (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|170th Street]]\n|-\n|express\n|&nbsp;\n|&nbsp;\n| style=\"background:yellow\" | Limited service ({{abbr|NB|northbound}} only)\n|-\n|[[167th Street station (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|167th Street]]\n|[[149th Street\u2013Grand Concourse (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|149th Street\u2013Grand Concourse]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |local\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n|style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |[[138th Street\u2013Grand Concourse (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|138th Street\u2013Grand Concourse]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |express\n|&nbsp;\n|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[IRT Lexington Avenue Line]] (full line)\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[125th Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|125th Street]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Brooklyn Bridge\u2013City Hall (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Brooklyn Bridge\u2013City Hall]]\n|style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| style=\"background:orange\" | Special events ({{abbr|SB|southbound}} only)\n|-\n| local\n| &nbsp;\n| rowspan=4 style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| [[Fulton Street (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Fulton Street]]\n| [[Bowling Green (IRT Lexington Avenue Line)|Bowling Green]]\n| rowspan=2 | all\n| rowspan=4 style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| rowspan=4 style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n|-\n| colspan=3 align=center | [[Joralemon Street Tunnel]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | [[IRT Eastern Parkway Line]] (full line)\n| [[Borough Hall (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Borough Hall]]\n| [[Nevins Street (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Nevins Street]]\n| rowspan=2 | express\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center]]\n| rowspan=2 | [[Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue (IRT Eastern Parkway Line)|Crown Heights\u2013Utica Avenue]]\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| local\n| rowspan=2 | &nbsp;\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:gray\" | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| [[IRT New Lots Line]] (full line)\n| [[Sutter Avenue\u2013Rutland Road (IRT New Lots Line)|Sutter Avenue\u2013Rutland Road]]\n| [[New Lots Avenue (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]]\n| all\n| style=\"background:yellow\" | Limited service\n|}\n\n=== Stations ===\n\nFor a more detailed station listing, see the articles on the lines listed above.<ref name=\"timetable\"/>\n{{NYCS service legend\n| alltimes = show\n| allexceptnights = show\n| nightsonly = show\n| nightsweekends = show\n| weekdaysonly = show\n| allexceptrush = show\n| allexceptweekdays =\n| dailyexceptrush =\n| rushonly = show\n| rushpeak = \n| weekdayspeak = \n| closed =\n| custom_icon_1 = rushpeak\n| custom_text_1 = Stops rush hours in the peak direction only (limited service)\n| custom_icon_2 = \n| custom_text_2 = \n}}\n{{Clear}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\" summary=\"Service information for the 4 train and its stations, including service times, ADA-accessibility, subway transfers, and non-subway connections.\"\n! width=6% colspan=2 | [[File:NYCS-bull-trans-4-Std.svg|20px|4 service to Woodlawn]]<br>{{abbr|Wood|Woodlawn}}\n! width=3% | [[File:NYCS-bull-trans-4-Std.svg|20px|4 service to Burnside Avenue]]<br>{{abbr|Burn|Burnside express; northbound service only}}\n! width=3% | [[File:NYCS-bull-trans-4-Std.svg|20px|4 service to 161st Street]]<br>{{abbr|161|161 Street special event express; southbound only}}\n! width=28% | Stations\n! width=3% | {{Access icon}}\n! width=36% | Subway transfers\n! width=27% | Connections/Notes\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" | '''[[The Bronx]]'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" | '''[[IRT Jerome Avenue Line|Jerome Avenue Line]]'''\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center rowspan=6 {{N/A}}\n| align=center rowspan=11 {{N/A}}\n| [[Woodlawn (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Woodlawn]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| [[Mosholu Parkway (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Mosholu Parkway]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| [[Bedford Park Boulevard\u2013Lehman College (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Bedford Park Boulevard\u2013Lehman College]]\n|\n|\n| Some southbound rush hour trips begin at this station<br />Some northbound p.m. rush hour trips terminate at this station\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| [[Kingsbridge Road (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Kingsbridge Road]]\n|\n|\n| Some southbound p.m. rush hour trips begin at this station\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| [[Fordham Road (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Fordham Road]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n|\n| [[Bx12 SBS (New York City bus)|Bx12 Select Bus Service]]\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| [[183rd Street (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|183rd Street]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[Burnside Avenue (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Burnside Avenue]]\n|\n|\n| Some northbound rush hour trips terminate at this station\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n|align=center |\u2191\n| [[176th Street (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|176th Street]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n|align=center |\u2191\n| [[Mount Eden Avenue (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|Mount Eden Avenue]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n|align=center |\u2191\n| [[170th Street (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|170th Street]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| [[167th Street (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|167th Street]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=center colspan=2 | {{NYCS SSI|alltimes}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|limitedrush}}\n| align=center | {{NYCS SSI|nightsonly}}\n| [[161st Street\u2013Yankee Stadium (IRT Jerome Avenue Line)|161st Street\u2013Yankee Stadium]]\n| align=center | {{Access icon}}\n| {{NYCS Concourse local|time=show}} ([[IND Concourse Line]])\n| [[Bx6 SBS (New York City bus)|Bx6 Select Bus Service]] <br> Northern term