athyan (actor)|Sathyan]], [[Sheela]], Maya || Malayalam film\n|-\n|44\n| 1971 || [[Pattondru Ketten]] || || [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]], [[Nagesh]] || \n|-\n|45\n| 1971 || [[Poi Sollathey]] || || [[Rajasree]] ||\n|-\n|46\n| 1971 || [[Agnimrigam]] || Vijayan || [[Prem Nazir]], [[Sathyan (actor)|Sathyan]], [[Sheela]] || Malayalam film\n|-\n|47\n| 1972 || [[Aromalunni]] || Kannappanunni<br>Chandrappan || [[Prem Nazir]], [[Sheela]], [[Vijayasree]] || Malayalam film\n|-\n|48\n| 1972 || [[Omana]] || Baby || [[Prem Nazir]], [[Sheela]], [[Rani Chandra]] || Malayalam film\n|-\n|49\n| 1972 || [[Ellai Kodu]] || || [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]], [[Vijayasree]] ||\n|-\n|50\n| 1972 || [[Puguntha Veedu (film)|Puguntha Veedu]] || || [[A. V. M. Rajan]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]], [[Lakshmi (actress)|Lakshmi]], [[Chandrakala]] ||\n|-\n|51\n| 1972 || [[Sakthi (1972 film)|Sakthi]] || || [[Sheela]], [[Thikkurissy Sukumaran Nair]] || Malayalam film\n|-\n|52\n| 1973 || [[Manjal Kungumam]] || || [[Sheela]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]] || \n|-\n|53\n| 1973 || [[Valli Deivanai]] || || [[Prameela]] ||\n|-\n|54\n| 1973 || [[Veettukku Vandha Marumagal]] || || [[A. V. M. Rajan]], [[Vennira Aadai Nirmala]], [[Latha (actress)|Latha]] ||\n|-\n|55\n| 1973 || [[Baghdad Perazhagi]] || Abdullah || [[Jayalalithaa]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]] || \n|-\n|56\n| 1974 || [[Pathu Madha Bandham]] || || [[Bhanumathi Ramakrishna|P. Bhanumathi]], [[B. Saroja Devi]], [[A. V. M. Rajan]], [[R. Muthuraman]], [[Vennira Aadai Nirmala]], [[Rajasree]] || Guest Appearance\n|-\n|57\n| 1974 || [[:ta:\u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe \u0b85\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe|Appa Amma]] || || [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], [[Sheela]] ||\n|-\n|58\n| 1974 || [[Roshakkari]] || || [[R. Muthuraman]], [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Kumari Padmini]], A. Sakunthala ||\n|-\n|59\n| 1974 || [[Magalukkaga]] || || [[A. V. M. Rajan]], [[Jaya Guhanathan|Jaya]] || Guest Appearance\n|-\n|60\n| 1974 || [[Avalukku Nigar Avale]] || || [[Vennira Aadai Nirmala]] ||\n|-\n|61\n| 1974 || [[Sorgathil Thirumanam]] || || [[Latha (actress)|Latha]] ||\n|-\n|62\n| 1974 || [[Akkarai Pachai]] || || [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]], [[Jaishankar]], [[Lakshmi (actress)|Lakshmi]], [[Jayachitra]], [[Rajasree]] ||\n|-\n|63\n| 1974 || [[Pudhiya Manidhan]] || || [[Vijaya Nirmala]], [[Jayasudha]] ||\n|-\n|64\n| 1975 || Amudha || || [[R. Muthuraman]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]], [[Rajasree]] ||\n|-\n|65\n| 1975 || Engalukkum Kadhal Varum || || [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]] ||\n|-\n|66\n| 1975 || Thai Veetu Seedhanam || || [[Jaishankar]], [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Ushanandini]] ||\n|-\n|67\n| 1975 || [[Avalukku Aayiram Kangal]] || || [[Jayalalithaa]], [[Jaishankar]] ||\n|-\n|68\n|1976 || [[Varaprasadham (1976 film)|Varaprasadham]] || || ||\n|-\n|69\n|1976 ||Janaki sabatham || || ||\n|-\n|70\n|1977||Nee Vaazha Vendum || || ||\n|-\n|70\n|1978||Iravu 12 Mani || || ||\n|-\n|71\n|1979||[[Neeya?]]||Ravi|| ||\n|-\n|72\n|1979||[[Kavari Maan]] || || ||\n|-\n|73\n|1979||[[Sikharangal]] || || ||Malayalam film\n|-\n|74\n|1980||Bombay Mail 109 || || ||\n|-\n|75\n|1985||[[Sugamana Raagangal]]|| || ||\n|-\n|76\n|1986||[[Amman Kovil Kizhakale]]|| Kanmani's father|| ||\n|-\n|77\n|1986||[[Oomai Vizhigal]]||P.R.K|| ||\n|-\n|78\n|1986||[[Murattuk Karangal]]||Muthu|| ||\n|-\n|79\n|1987||[[Neethikku Thandanai]] || || ||\n|-\n|80\n|1987||[[Ninaive Oru Sangeetham]] || || ||\n|-\n|81\n|1987||[[Sattam Oru Vilayaattu]] || DCP Needhi Manikkam || ||\n|-\n|82\n|1987||[[Ivargal Varungala Thoongal]] || || ||\n|-\n|83\n|1988||[[Guru Sishyan (1988 film)|Guru Sishyan]]||Rajamanickam|| ||\n|-\n|84\n|1988||[[Therkathi Kallan]] || || ||\n|-\n|85\n|1989||[[Raja Chinna Roja]] || || ||\n|-\n|86\n|1989 ||[[Sattathin Thirappu Vizhaa]]||Ethiraj|| ||\n|-\n|87\n|1989||Oru Thottil Sabadham || || ||\n|-\n|88\n|1989||[[Chinnappadass]] || || ||\n|-\n|89\n|1990||[[Paattukku Naan Adimai]] || || ||\n|-\n|90\n|1990||[[Naanum Indha Ooruthan]] || || ||\n|-\n|91\n|1991||[[Manitha Jaathi]] || || ||\n|-\n|92\n|1992||[[Sevagan]] || || ||\n|-\n|93\n|1993||[[Pudhiya Mugam]] || || ||\n|-\n|94\n|1994||[[En Rajangam]]|| Kodandam|| ||\n|-\n|95\n|1995||[[Karnaa|Karna]]|| Arjun's father|| ||\n|-\n|96\n|1997||[[Arunachalam (film)|Arunachalam]] || || ||\n|-\n|97\n|1999||[[Maanaseega Kadhal]] || || || Also director\n|-\n|98\n|2002||[[Pammal K. Sambandam]] || || ||\n|-\n|99\n|2002||[[Ramana (film)|Ramana]] || || ||\n|-\n|100\n|2003||[[Thennavan]] || || ||\n|-\n|101\n|2003||Indru Mudhal || || ||\n|-\n|102\n|2003||[[Tagore (film)|Tagore]] || || || Telugu film\n|-\n|103\n|2004||[[Thendral (film)|Thendral]]|| Singara Velu Nayagar|| ||\n|-\n|104\n|2005 ||[[Manthiran]] || || || Also director\n|-\n|105\n|2006||[[Adaikalam]] || || ||\n|-\n|106\n|2008||[[Arasangam]] || || ||\n|-\n|107\n|2009||[[Kanden Kadhalai]] || || ||\n|-\n|108\n|2011||[[Aadu Puli]] || || ||\n|-\nOk\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb name|id=1119422|name=Ravichandran}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ravichandran}}\n[[Category:2011 deaths]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian emigrants to India]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Tiruchirappalli]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Chennai]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian film directors]]\n[[Category:Tamil film directors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:People from Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Chennai]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Ravichandran\n| image = Ravichandran (Tamil actor).jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_date =\n| death_date = 25 Jul 2011\n| death_place = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India\n| birth_place = [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]\n| birth_name = B.S. Raman\n| occupation = Actor, director, Agriculturist\n| years_active = 1964\u20132011\n| spouse = Vimala<br />[[Sheela]] (divorced)\n| children = [[Hamsavardhan]](Actor),<br>[[George Vishnu]](Actor),<br>Lavanya Sriram,<br>S.r.Balaji(businessman)(died 13th may 2018)\n| relatives = [[Tanya Ravichandran]] (granddaughter)\n}}\n\n'''Ravichandran''' (d. 25 July 2011) was a Malaysian Indian actor who played lead hero roles in Tamil films from 1964 to 1979. He has also aced in supporting roles from 1986, and directed a few films.<ref>{{cite news|title=Actor Ravichandran's directorial venture|author=S. R. Ashok Kumar|url=http://www.hindu.com/2005/11/25/stories/2005112505780200.htm|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=25 November 2005|location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2005/12/22/stories/2005122218050200.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Ravichandran on how he got into Tamil films | date=22 December 2005}}</ref> \n\nHe was given the title of \"Kalaingnar Thilagham\" in many of the on-screen credits of films starring him in the lead role. He was also called \"Puratchi Kalaignar\" (Refer: Anandha Bairavi Tamil Movie Title Scene). Before entering cinema, during his studies in Trichy, he has acted in two dramas, namely, ''AanaiyidungalAnna'' and ''Udhaya Suriyan''. After entering cinema, he has acted in two dramas, namely, ''Mapplley Yen Magalaik Kadhali'' and ''That Man from Poonthamallee''. In the drama ''That man from Poonthamallee'', he performed in a double role and Thirumuruga Kirupanandha Variyar, who presided over the drama in Vellore, has appreciated and awarded him the title \"Nadaga Sigamani\". He has also acted in a TV serial, namely, ''GEE Boom Ba'' in 1986. He has also made a Guest Role in a Hindi Movie \"Nanha Farishta\" with Vennira Aadai Nirmala. His dance performance in \"Nanha Farista\" was super and excellent. During his tenure of acting, his fans, journalists and movie-directors/producers have given many titles, viz., Kalai Ulaga Ilavarasar, Kalai Nilavu, Romantic Hero, Velli Vizha Kathanayagan, Vannap Pada Nayagan,  Evergreen Hero, Chinna MGR, Kalaignar Thilagam, Style King, Stunt Man an, Bhagdath Perazhagan, Kalai Chelvan, Pudhumai Thilagam etc. He was very affectionate with his fans.\n\n== Life ==\nRavichandran is a [[Tamil language|Tamil]], born B.S. Raman in [[Kuala Lumpur]], capital of the [[Federated Malay States]]. He moved to [[Tiruchirappalli]], India in 1951, and studied at the [[St. Joseph's College, Tiruchirappalli|St. Joseph's College]]. He was married twice; he first married Vimala, with whom he has a daughter, Lavanya, and two sons, Balaji and [[Hamsavardhan]]. Thereafter, he married Malayalam actress [[Sheela]], and had a son George. His sons Hamsavardhan and George also took up acting as a career, with Hamsavardhan starring in the film ''Manthiran'', directed by Ravichandran himself. Lavanya is married and has two daughters. His granddaughter [[Tanya Ravichandran]] debuted through ''[[Balle Vellaiyathevaa]]'', playing alongside [[M. Sasikumar]]\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:70%;\"\n|-\n!S.No. \n! Year !! Film !!  Role !! Co-Star !!  Notes\n|-\n|1\n| 1964 || ''[[Kaadhalikka Neramillai]]'' || Ashok || [[R. Muthuraman]], [[Rajasree]], [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]], [[Nagesh]] || Debut film\n|-\n|2\n| 1965 || [[Idhayak Kamalam]] || || [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Sheela]] ||\n|-\n|3\n| 1965 || [[Kalyana Mandapam (1965 film)|Kalyana Mandapam]] || || C. L. Anandan, [[K. R. Vijaya]], Malathi ||\n|-\n|4\n| 1966 || [[Motor Sundaram Pillai]] || || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Sowcar Janaki]], Manimala, [[Jayalalithaa]] ||\n|-\n|5\n| 1966 || [[Kumari Penn]] || Kanthan || [[Jayalalithaa]] ||\n|-\n|6\n| 1966 || Thedi Vandha Thirumagal || || [[S. S. Rajendran]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]], [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]] ||\n|-\n|7\n| 1966 || [[Enga Pappa]] || || [[Bharathi Vishnuvardhan|Bharathi]], [[Nagesh]] ||\n|-\n|8\n| 1966 || [[Naam