 {{Start date|2017|6|13|df=y}}\n| Viewers         = 2.42<ref name=\"Premiere\" />\n| ShortSummary    = The robbers initiate a plan to use the hostages to stall the police and gain more time, but Raquel takes the chance to reveal a secret that Berlin has kept from the others\u2014he only has a few months left to live due to a terminal illness\u2014increasing the mistrust among them and makes an attempt to convince Rio to surrender.\n| LineColor       = A90712\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = T\u00fa lo has buscado\n| AltTitle        = You Asked for It\n| DirectedBy      = Alejandro Bazzano\n| WrittenBy       = \u00c1lex Pina, Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, Javier G\u00f3mez Santander, Pablo Roa & Fernando Sancrist\u00f3bal\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|6|20|df=y}}\n| Viewers         = 2.07<ref name=\"Premiere\" />\n| ShortSummary    = Raquel loses her trust in \u00c1ngel, who is unaware of the bug the robbers planted in his glasses, while Arturo prepares another plan to escape, but becomes devastated upon discovering M\u00f3nica and Denver's affair. \u00c1ngel, who is taken off the case, is in a [[coma]] after a car accident while drunk, discovered the Professor's identity through fingerprints taken from his cider factory\u2014a front for his hideout.\n| LineColor       = A90712\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = El que la sigue la consigue\n| AltTitle        = Whoever Keeps Trying It, Gets It\n| DirectedBy      = Jes\u00fas Colmenar\n| WrittenBy       = \u00c1lex Pina, Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, Javier G\u00f3mez Santander, Pablo Roa, Fernando Sancrist\u00f3bal & Esther Morales\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|6|27|df=y}}\n| Viewers         = 2.19<ref name=\"Premiere\" />\n| ShortSummary    = Thanks to Arturo's plan, 16 hostages manage to escape and Oslo is on the brink of death after he is beaten by some of the hostages. Before his car accident, 